Her beauty in the eyes of azure was for a long time her trump card, some will say her weakness.
Had he freed himself from the narcissistic mirror, the American actor with the charming smile?
Yes and no.
His modesty, sensitivity and a talent that flowed from the source will also have moved him away from the power register that gives birth to the true sacred monsters.
What a great runner!
Paul Newman, who died Friday at the age of 83 from lung cancer on his Connecticut ranch, remains one of the last icons of American cinema in his heyday.
Less monumental than Brando, to whom he resembled and of whom he was for a long time a sort of rival on the screen, more cautious in his play, certainly more fragile, but also apostle of freedom and the shattering of dramatic conventions.
Mixed blood often makes beautiful children.
