With a final role as godfather of the Irish mafia in Sam Mendes’ Road to Perdition in 2003, the loop was closed.
Contrary to several film legends who dropped the profession early enough, Newman will have remained in the saddle for a long time, while denouncing Hollywood, its gold, its pomp and its concessions.
The French filmmaker Bertrand Tavernier considered it, not without humor, "as a living challenge to "underplaying" judging his performances too supported.
