Her Rachel, Rachel, in 1968 (based on the novel by Canadian author Margaret Laurence), with his wife Joanne Woodward in the title role, painted a fine female portrait of melancholy.
He who lost his son Scott by overdose dedicated his film Harry and Son in 1984, a work of modesty and sadness.
