Industrial export sales prices increased by 1.1 per cent compared to July 2008, while compared to a year earlier they decreased by 3.9 per cent.
As a result of fluctuations in domestic and export prices, industrial producer prices increased by 0.7 per cent compared to the previous month and by 3.2 per cent compared to the previous year.
Domestic industrial sales prices increased only to a lesser extent: by 0.1 per cent, compared to the previous month.
Domestic sales prices in the processing industry sectors were up only a tiny 0.1 per cent compared to July.
