The higher price level of plastics and chemical raw materials has resulted in a significant monthly increase in the prices of the chemical products and materials manufacturing sector (1.6 per cent).
This resulted in deflation in the oil processing (1.4 per cent), electrical machinery and equipment manufacturing (0.9 per cent) and a minimal increase in the wood processing sector (0.1 per cent).
